Solvent extraction (D2EHPA-based),"D2EHPA (di-(2-ethylhexyl) phosphoric acid) at 0.3, 0.6, 0.9, 1.2 M in various diluents (Solvent 70, hexane, octane, toluene, cyclohexanone, 1-octanol, chloroform); stripping with HCl (0.5–3 M)","Nd, Dy, Pr, Gd (plus monitoring Co and B as contaminants)",Real NdFeB magnet leachate produced via selective roasting/sulfation and sulfuric acid leaching (commercially relevant magnet waste leachate),"Extraction: up to 100% transfer of REEs to organic phase at 0.9–1.2 M D2EHPA in hexane/octane; selective HREE extraction (Dy, Gd ~~99%) with 0.3 M D2EHPA in hexane while LREEs ~50% under those conditions; Stripping: ~100% at ≥2 M HCl",Highest Dy/Nd (aDy/Nd) separation achieved with 0.3 M D2EHPA in hexane (numerical values: Dy/Gd high; many separation factors reported in Table 2 — best Dy/(Nd&Pr) with 0.3 M hexane; typical adjacent-REE separation factors with D2EHPA ~2.5; other diluents/concentrations gave aDy/Nd <10,Extraction kinetics: equilibrium reached <3 min in most diluents (3–5 min in cyclohexanone/chloroform); experimental equilibration and stripping used 20 min shaking for re-equilibration and 5 min stripping tests,D2EHPA used at 0.3–1.2 M; HCl stripping at 0.5–3 M. No mass-based reagent consumption (kg reagent per kg REE) reported.,Not mentioned in source.,General statement: solvent extraction can give materials up to 99.99% purity (cited). This paper does not report final purified product purities from a full process flow or precipitation steps.,Bench-scale batch tests at 3.5 mL vials; TRL: lab-scale (no pilot studies reported),Not mentioned in source.
"Solvent extraction following acetic acid leaching (D2EHPA in kerosene, 30% v/v) with contact time ~20 min at 30°C; technology type: solvent extraction (post-acid leaching)","Leaching reagent: acetic acid (CH3COOH), 1 M; extractant: D2EHPA in kerosene (30% v/v); phase ratio A:O = 1:1",Neodymium (Nd) and Dysprosium (Dy),"Xenotime mineral leachate (primary mineral source), not magnet manufacturing waste",Nd: 99.4%; Dy: 99.3%,Not mentioned in source.,Contact time: 20 minutes at 30°C (optimal),Leachant concentration: 1 M acetic acid; organic phase D2EHPA 30% v/v; A:O phase ratio 1:1. Specific reagent consumption per kg REE not mentioned,Not mentioned in source.,Not mentioned in source.,Laboratory-scale study on xenotime leachates; TRL: laboratory (bench-scale),Not mentioned in source.
Not mentioned in source.,"TODGA (tetraoctyl diglycolamide) and D2EHPA (di(2-ethylhexyl)phosphoric acid) were used as extractants; leachates prepared in nitric acid (for TODGA) and sulfuric acid (for D2EHPA); diluents tested included solvent 70, hexane, octane, cyclohexanone, toluene, 1-octanol and chloroform.","Neodymium (Nd), Dysprosium (Dy), with minor Praseodymium (Pr) and Terbium (Tb).",Real neodymium magnet waste leachates: nitric acid and sulfuric acid media leachates from commercial neodymium magnet waste.,Not mentioned in source.,"Authors report that diluent choice affected separation factors and that both extractants showed good selectivity for REEs, but specific numerical separation factors are Not mentioned in source..",Not mentioned in source.,Not mentioned in source.,Not mentioned in source.,Not mentioned in source.,Lab-scale research using real commercial leachates; TRL appears to be research/lab stage (not a pilot or commercial deployment) based on description.,Not mentioned in source.
